Author Name: **Pinhas Krengel**
Original Redmine Message: 1084 from https://www.veripool.org



---

Hi

I am new to verilator. I have problems in driving data to a simple single clock DUT.
If clock edge and data stimuli is driven at the same time (delta=0), DUT registered outputs, 
behave as combinatorial ones.
If I delay the data drive in one, I see problems in the next cycle as -> eval sees the data drive change 
too late.
I have also tried with no delay where the evaluation is done in between clock edge and data 
drive.
My code is attached. Can you please tell what is wrong or post a recommended way to drive clock 
and data.

  while (!Verilated::gotFinish()) {
     if (main_time > 10) {
       pipe_fifo_tool->rst = 0;   // Deassert reset
     }
     if ((main_time % 10) == 1) {
       pipe_fifo_tool->clk = 1;       // Toggle clock
     }
     if ((main_time % 10) == 6) {
       pipe_fifo_tool->clk = 0;
     }

     if (((main_time-delta) % 10) == 1) {
       //cout << "sim gen :time is " << main_time << endl;       // Read a output
       entry.ti=main_time;
       entry.fe=pipe_fifo_tool->fe;
       entry.ff=pipe_fifo_tool->ff;
       gen(entry);
       //drive using c2v DPI function
       t_gen_stim(entry.rd, entry.wr);
       //pipe_fifo_tool->t_gen_stim(entry.rd, entry.wr);
       //Vpipe_fifo_tool::t_gen_stim(entry.rd, entry.wr);
     }

     pipe_fifo_tool->eval();

Thanks
Pinhas
